lovely /ˈlʌvlɪ/

(lovelier,loveliest) 

1. ADJ If you describe someone or something as lovely , you mean that they are very beautiful and therefore pleasing to look at or listen to. 美丽的; 美妙的 

例： You look lovely, Marcia. 你看起来很美，马西娅。 

例： He had a lovely voice. 他嗓音甜美。 

2. loveliness N-UNCOUNT 漂亮 

例： You are a vision of loveliness. 你貌美如画。 

3. ADJ If you describe something as lovely , you mean that it gives you pleasure. 令人愉快的 [口语] 

例： Mary! How lovely to see you! 玛丽，见到你多么愉快！ 

例： It's a lovely day. 天气很好。

</div>

